Functionality Checklist
This checklist summarizes all of the functionality you are expected to build. This will be used to assess the completion of your project:

Main Menu:

Y User is shown the main menu where they can play or quit

Setup:

Y Computer can place ships randomly in valid locations
Y User can enter valid sequences to place both ships
Y Entering invalid ship placements prompts user to enter valid placements

Turn:

Y User board is displayed showing hits, misses, sunken ships, and ships
Y Computer board is displayed showing hits, misses, and sunken ships
Y Computer chooses a random shot
Y Computer does not fire on the same spot twice
Y User can choose a valid coordinate to fire on
Y Entering invalid coordinate prompts user to enter valid coordinate
Y Both computer and player shots are reported as a hit, sink, or miss
Y User is informed when they have already fired on a coordinate
Y Board is updated after a turn

End Game:

Y Game ends when all the user’s ships are sunk
Y Game ends when all the computer’s ships are sunk
Y Game reports who won
Y Game returns user back to the Main Menu
